Table
Of
Contents
<!--mvp-post-img-hide--
>
Cybersecurity
is
becoming
increasingly
crucial
for
businesses
in
every
sector,
and
it
is
especially
vital
for
small-
to
medium-sized
organizations.
Cyberattacks
continue
to
become
a
major
problem
in
the
United
States
and
the
rest
of
the
globe,
often
times
resulting
in
customer
information
being
stolen.
Because
of
this
increased
risk,
cybersecurity
certifications
are
an
important
tool
to
prepare
against
the
attacks.
The
high
demand
for
cybersecurity
skills
means
a
top
cybersecurity
certification
will
boost
one’s
resumé.
With
so
many
cybersecurity
certifications
to
choose
from,
let’s
take
a
look
at
the
top
ones
on
the
market:
1.
IBM
Cybersecurity
Analyst
Professional
Certificate
The
IBM
Cybersecurity
Analyst
course
was
designed
from
the
ground-up
to
prepare
you
for
the
real-world
of
hacker
attacks.
You
can
get
enrolled
for
free.
Investigate
a
real-world
security
breach
identifying
the
attack,
vulnerabilities,
costs
and
prevention
recommendations.
This
8-course
Professional
Certificate
will
give
you
the
technical
skills
to
become
job-ready
for
a
Cybersecurity
Analyst
role.
Instructional
content
and
labs
will
introduce
you
to
concepts
including
network
security,
endpoint
protection,
incident
response,
threat
intelligence,
penetration
testing,
and
vulnerability
assessment.
2.
Cybersecurity
Mastertrack
Certificate
The
Cybersecurity
Mastertrack
Certificate
by
Arizona
State
University
(ASU)
is
designed
to
provide
IT
professionals
with
the
knowledge
needed
to
manage
vulnerabilities
in
an
enterprise.
Build
and
practice
essential
cybersecurity
skills
by
studying
cryptography,
software
security,
network
security,
and
more
from
the
#1
ranked
school
for
innovation
in
the
U.S.
In
this
program,
you
will
complete
a
real
module
from
the
online
Master
of
Computer
Science
program
that
will
help
you
understand
the
field
of
Cybersecurity
through
the
lens
of
computer
systems
and
algorithms.
You
will
learn
to
protect
and
defend
information
and
information
systems
by
ensuring
their
availability,
integrity,
authentication,
confidentiality,
and
non-repudiation
through
protection,
detection,
and
reaction
practices.
3.
CompTIA
Security+
Certification
Training
Another
top
certification
is
the
CompTIA
Security+
offers
you
a
chance
to
earn
a
global
certification
that
focuses
on
core
cybersecurity
skills
which
are
indispensable
for
security
and
network
administrators.
The
course
is
ideal
to validate
your
skill
set
in
risk
management,
risk
mitigation,
threat
management,
and
intrusion
detection.
This
CompTIA
Security+
certification
enables
you
to
handle
security
incidents,
not
just
identify
them.
You&#8217;ll
soon
be
able
to
explain
different
threat
actors,
vectors,
and
intelligence
sources,
and
more
importantly
analyze
potential
indicators
associated
with
application
and
network
attacks.
4.
Edureka’s
Cybersecurity
Certification
Course
This
course
was
developed
in
order
to
get
you
thinking
like
a
hacker,
which
is
crucial
to
stop
one.
The
class
covers
various
topics
and
tools
such
as
hacking
technologies
that
are
used
against
cloud
computing
technology,
mobile
platforms
and
operating
systems.
Throughout
the
course,
you
will
learn
important
concepts
such
as
ethical
hacking,
cryptography,
computer
networks
&amp;
security,
application
security,
idAM
(identity
&amp;
access
management),
vulnerability
analysis,
malware
threats,
sniffing,
SQL
injection,
DoS,
session
hijacking,
and
various
security
practices
for
businesses
along
with
hands-on
demonstration
5.
CompTIA
Security+
The
CompTIA
Security+
is
another
top
base-level
certification
for
IT
professionals.
It
only
requires
two
years
of
experience
to
complete,
and
it
is
considered
a
general
cybersecurity
certification
since
it
is
also
useful
for
a
variety
of
setups.
The
ComptTIA
Security+
covers
topics
like
network
attack
strategies
and
defenses,
effective
security
policies,
network-
and
host-based
security
practices,
disaster
recovery
and
encryption
standards
and
products.
This
certification
is
useful
for
those
looking
to
become
more
knowledgeable
in
basic
IT
security.
It
applies
to
all
job
roles,
especially
developers,
PC
support
analysts,
and
accounting
managers.
The
U.S.
Department
of
Defense
requires
it
for
all
employees.
6.
Certified
Information
Security
Manager
(CISM)
The
Certified
Information
Security
Manager
Certification
(CISM)
is
considered
one
of
the
best
cybersecurity
courses
on
the
market.
It
requires
at
least
five
years
of
experience.
The
CISM
is
management-focused,
and
it
covers
four
specific
topics:
Information
security
program
development
and
management
Information
security
management
Information
security
incident
management
Information
risk
management
and
compliance
The
CISM
is
significantly
more
rigorous
than
others,
but
it
is
useful
for
CISO’s
and
other
IT
professionals.
7.
NIST
Cybersecurity Professional
(NCSP)
 
The
NIST
Cybersecurity
Framework
was
built
in
2014,
and
by
2015,
30
percent
or
U.S.
organizations
were
using
it.
The
certifications
in
the
NCSF
provide
the
skills
to
design,
build,
test
and
manage
cybersecurity
programs
with
the
framework.
The
two
certifications
currently
available
within
the
NCSP
Progamme
are:
NCSF
Foundation
Certification:
This
program
is
aimed
at
executives,
business
professionals
and
IT
professionals
looking
for
a
basic
grasp
on
NCSF.
It
is
specifically
used
to
establish
common
NCSF
vocabulary
across
a
company.
&nbsp;
NCSF
Practitioner
Certification:
This
program
is
for
designing
and
building
comprehensive
cybersecurity
programs,
and
it
teaches
you
how
to
minimize
risks
and
protect
critical
assets
through
a
business-focused
cybersecurity
risk
management
program.
Additional
NCSP
Specialist
programmes
are
set
to
be
released
in
early
2021.
8.
Certified
Cloud
Security
Professional
(CCSP)
The
CCSP
certification
provides
IT
professionals
with
hands-on
experience,
which
will
lead
to
efficiency
in
cloud
security
architecture,
design,
operations
and
services.
It
is
specifically
targeted
at
security
professionals
with
experience
in
information
technology,
IT
architecture,
governance,
cloud
and
web
security
engineering.
CCSP,
which
also
requires
a
minimum
of
five
years
of
experience,
covers
various
topics
such
as
cloud
architecture
and
design
concepts,
cloud
data
security,
cloud
operations,
infrastructure
security
and
compliance.
It
is
especially
useful
for
systems
engineers,
security
managers,
security
administrators
and
enterprise
architects.
9.
Cisco
Certified
Network
Associate
(CCNA)
Security
 
The
CCNA
provides
the
specific
knowledge
and
hands-on
skills
needed
to
protect
Cisco
networks,
so
it
is
valuable
for
organizations
deploying
Cisco
technology.
It
is
an
associate-level
certification
that
helps
you
recognize
threats
in
a
Cisco
network,
as
well
as
develop
effective
security
infrastructure.
It
is
especially
valuable
for
network
security
specialists,
network
support
engineers
and
security
administrators.
10.
Computer
Hacking
Forensic
Investigator
(CHFI)
 
The
CHFI
is
an
advanced
certification
aimed
at
forensic
network
security
investigators.
It
provides
the
skills
needed
to
gather
evidence
and
prosecute
in
court.
CHFI
covers
topics
such
as
incident
response
and
forensics,
information
recovery,
technical
examination
and
analysis,
and
computer-based
evidence
reporting.
With
the
increase
in
cyber
threats
in
every
sector,
there
should
be
a
major
push
to
obtain
these
top
cybersecurity
certifications.
There
are
many
great
options
on
the
market,
for
every
level
of
an
organization.
Each
one
provides
the
specific
skills
needed
to
address
cybersecurity
issues,
and
they
provide
businesses
with
the
opportunity
to
prepare
their
IT
staff
for
the
ever-evolving
digital
environment.
